1
00:00:00,167 --> 00:00:01,573
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,573 --> 00:00:03,002
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,538 --> 00:00:05,939
(Episode 15)

4
00:00:07,826 --> 00:00:10,660
Since I'm here,
maybe I'll see Eun Ae before I leave.

5
00:00:11,820 --> 00:00:13,046
The Strategic Planning Division is...

6
00:00:19,319 --> 00:00:21,712
Excuse me. Can I ask you something?

7
00:00:22,159 --> 00:00:24,224
Which floor
is the Strategic Planning Division on?

8
00:00:27,965 --> 00:00:28,965
Excuse me.

9
00:00:33,180 --> 00:00:36,014
What? Is he saying it's the fifth floor?

10
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:39,000
Unbelievable.

11
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,267
What kind of woman does that?

12
00:00:42,219 --> 00:00:44,978
Hey, I'm burning up inside.

13
00:00:44,978 --> 00:00:46,834
Let's grab an iced coffee before we go.

14
00:00:49,693 --> 00:00:50,693
Okay.

15
00:00:55,167 --> 00:00:56,552
Seriously.

16
00:00:57,746 --> 00:00:58,746
I'm so mad.

17
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:02,598
Look at her with her little minion.

18
00:01:03,393 --> 00:01:04,931
Who does she think she is, a queen?

19
00:01:14,039 --> 00:01:15,039
Hey, Eun Ae.

20
00:01:15,373 --> 00:01:18,473
I'm in the Kangsu Construction lobby.

21
00:01:24,959 --> 00:01:28,240
What's going on? Why is she here?

22
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,262
I'm so mad I could die.

23
00:01:35,666 --> 00:01:37,066
What is with my luck today?

24
00:01:41,467 --> 00:01:42,600
Fancy running into you again.

25
00:01:43,942 --> 00:01:45,086
Yes.

26
00:01:45,819 --> 00:01:47,386
I'm here to see my daughter.

27
00:01:47,712 --> 00:01:49,700
She said she's busy and told me to wait.

28
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:52,067
Then why don't you sit here?

29
00:01:52,713 --> 00:01:55,246
We're in the same dance class.
Let's introduce ourselves.

30
00:01:56,380 --> 00:01:57,413
What's wrong with you?

31
00:01:58,473 --> 00:02:00,073
All right.

32
00:02:04,386 --> 00:02:06,586
Is your daughter an employee
at Kangsu Construction?

33
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:12,100
Yes, she used to run an AI company,

34
00:02:12,613 --> 00:02:15,846
but the people at Kangsu Construction were
so impressed with her program...

35
00:02:16,206 --> 00:02:19,872
that they practically begged her to join.

36
00:02:20,073 --> 00:02:24,034
She was recently scouted
to the Strategic Planning Division.

37
00:02:24,346 --> 00:02:26,413
The Strategic Planning Division?

38
00:02:26,633 --> 00:02:29,083
Yes. The Strategic Planning Division.

39
00:02:30,972 --> 00:02:32,106
Look here.

40
00:02:32,634 --> 00:02:34,407
My son works in the Strategic Planning...

41
00:02:34,407 --> 00:02:35,413
My goodness.

42
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:40,434
You must be so proud
of your talented daughter.

43
00:02:41,659 --> 00:02:44,927
It feels a bit like bragging,

44
00:02:45,646 --> 00:02:48,312
but my son is a professor,

45
00:02:49,053 --> 00:02:50,620
and my youngest daughter is a doctor.

46
00:02:50,985 --> 00:02:52,534
That's something to be proud of.

47
00:02:52,973 --> 00:02:55,339
How did you raise your children so well?

48
00:02:57,145 --> 00:02:58,178
What year did you enter college?

49
00:02:58,793 --> 00:03:01,314
I entered in 1988, French literature.

50
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:03,860
In 1988?

51
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,846
Mine is 2030.

52
00:03:08,088 --> 00:03:09,790
What? 2030?

53
00:03:10,367 --> 00:03:14,234
Don't you mean 1930? That is also absurd.

54
00:03:14,234 --> 00:03:16,234
No, I'm currently a high school graduate,

55
00:03:16,506 --> 00:03:19,573
but I'm planning to enter in 2030.

56
00:03:20,834 --> 00:03:24,167
And asking someone's class year
like that...

57
00:03:24,319 --> 00:03:26,600
is rude, you know?

58
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,409
What?

59
00:03:33,367 --> 00:03:36,300
My daughter's here. I'll get going.

60
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:38,422
See you in class next time.

61
00:03:38,422 --> 00:03:39,422
Yes.

62
00:03:40,486 --> 00:03:42,419
Unbelievable. I'm so mad.

63
00:03:42,419 --> 00:03:43,657
I'm losing it.

64
00:03:43,967 --> 00:03:44,967
I'm losing it!

65
00:03:46,834 --> 00:03:47,834
Seriously!

66
00:03:54,213 --> 00:03:56,680
What's going on?
Why are you suddenly doing line dancing?

67
00:03:57,253 --> 00:03:59,483
It's been tough, hasn't it?

68
00:03:59,853 --> 00:04:02,267
It must be exhausting,

69
00:04:02,267 --> 00:04:04,434
handling all the planning work alone.

70
00:04:04,434 --> 00:04:06,767
No, I don't have anything to do.

71
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:07,767
I'm bored out of my mind.

72
00:04:07,767 --> 00:04:10,267
If they hired talent,

73
00:04:10,267 --> 00:04:13,100
they should support you properly.

74
00:04:13,287 --> 00:04:14,588
What are you talking about?

75
00:04:14,588 --> 00:04:17,234
Still, you're capable,

76
00:04:17,234 --> 00:04:20,427
so you have to grow the company.

77
00:04:21,020 --> 00:04:22,886
Who am I talking to right now?

78
00:04:24,913 --> 00:04:26,267
Play along a bit.

79
00:04:26,267 --> 00:04:29,867
I'm trying to put that woman behind us
in her place.

80
00:04:30,166 --> 00:04:31,166
What?

81
00:04:34,006 --> 00:04:35,006
Let's go.

82
00:04:42,193 --> 00:04:43,760
Seriously.

83
00:04:47,759 --> 00:04:49,195
You're home.

84
00:04:49,824 --> 00:04:51,091
I'll step out for a bit.

85
00:04:51,091 --> 00:04:53,300
Okay. Are you going on a date with Father?

86
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,667
No, it's not like that.

87
00:05:00,679 --> 00:05:02,461
Maid, get me some iced water!

88
00:05:02,461 --> 00:05:03,904
Yes, ma'am.

89
00:05:05,434 --> 00:05:07,700
No, I'm currently a high school graduate,

90
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:10,800
but I'm planning to enter in 2030.

91
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:15,234
And asking someone's class year
like that...

92
00:05:15,534 --> 00:05:17,784
is rude, you know?

93
00:05:18,087 --> 00:05:21,153
What? Starting in 2030? Rude?

94
00:05:22,119 --> 00:05:23,256
Seriously.

95
00:05:28,539 --> 00:05:30,664
What's that smell?

96
00:05:30,806 --> 00:05:33,099
Madam asked me to make...

97
00:05:33,099 --> 00:05:35,773
crab stew for dinner,
Master Gyeol's favorite.

98
00:05:35,773 --> 00:05:38,971
What? Master Gyeol? Listen!

99
00:05:41,006 --> 00:05:42,236
- Welcome back.
- Yes.

100
00:05:42,526 --> 00:05:43,560
You're home early.

101
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,760
- Yes.
- We're home.

102
00:05:45,473 --> 00:05:47,373
Where are Grandpa and Grandma?

103
00:05:48,187 --> 00:05:49,220
They went out on a date.

104
00:05:50,927 --> 00:05:53,360
They've been so lovey-dovey lately.

105
00:05:56,047 --> 00:05:58,013
He made her wear a dress...

106
00:05:58,013 --> 00:05:59,559
and took Mr. Ju along.

107
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,429
Like a real princess.

108
00:06:02,919 --> 00:06:06,131
They've always been affectionate.

109
00:06:06,131 --> 00:06:07,733
Is now really the time for that?

110
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:09,566
With his condition?

111
00:06:11,046 --> 00:06:13,667
They don't have much time,

112
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:15,834
so it means more to them.

113
00:06:17,179 --> 00:06:18,578
By the way, Crystal.

114
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:21,681
Why are you so worked up today?

115
00:06:21,681 --> 00:06:24,234
Don't even ask. I ran into...

116
00:06:24,486 --> 00:06:26,500
the most ridiculous woman at dance class.

117
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,222
My blood pressure's through the roof.

118
00:06:29,053 --> 00:06:31,086
Your blood pressure?

119
00:06:31,706 --> 00:06:33,740
That won't do. I can't be a widower.

120
00:06:33,740 --> 00:06:35,734
No, that won't do...

121
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:41,060
Let's take a deep breath.

122
00:06:43,573 --> 00:06:44,573
A deep breath.

123
00:06:47,067 --> 00:06:48,767
That's it, good.

124
00:06:49,339 --> 00:06:50,839
- Good.
- Like this?

125
00:06:50,839 --> 00:06:52,145
More, from the chest.

126
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,291
Did something good happen, Mom?

127
00:07:04,707 --> 00:07:05,792
What? Why?

128
00:07:06,253 --> 00:07:08,561
She's been like that
since she got back from dance class.

129
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:10,063
What is it?

130
00:07:10,063 --> 00:07:13,199
Something very satisfying happened.

131
00:07:14,583 --> 00:07:17,837
This has to do with Min Ho's mom,
doesn't it?

132
00:07:18,123 --> 00:07:20,700
You've got great intuition, my son.

133
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:22,376
You're silly.

134
00:07:23,763 --> 00:07:26,234
Did your team recently recruit...

135
00:07:26,234 --> 00:07:29,015
a woman who used to run an AI company?

136
00:07:29,442 --> 00:07:31,767
Yes. How do you know that?

137
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:35,126
So it wasn't a lie.

138
00:07:35,866 --> 00:07:39,108
At today's line dancing class,

139
00:07:39,581 --> 00:07:42,067
Min Ho's mom insisted...

140
00:07:42,067 --> 00:07:43,334
she had to be in the center...

141
00:07:43,334 --> 00:07:45,031
and put her water bottle down.

142
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:51,338
I'll get it myself.

143
00:07:52,093 --> 00:07:53,093
Gyeol,

144
00:07:54,212 --> 00:07:56,876
I hear you've been going out a lot lately.
Where to?

145
00:07:57,033 --> 00:08:00,330
Nothing specific. Just here and there.

146
00:08:00,330 --> 00:08:02,134
Here and there? That's not proper work.

147
00:08:02,483 --> 00:08:04,217
Isn't that neglecting your duties?

148
00:08:07,068 --> 00:08:08,600
Let me ask you something just in case.

149
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:11,234
Are you just going through the motions
in this race...

150
00:08:11,234 --> 00:08:13,126
because of Grandpa?

151
00:08:13,399 --> 00:08:14,399
Sorry?

152
00:08:15,098 --> 00:08:18,165
Partly, yes.

153
00:08:18,847 --> 00:08:19,947
Are you serious?

154
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:23,666
Why waste your time and talent like that?

155
00:08:23,666 --> 00:08:25,367
You left your work in the U.S. for this?

156
00:08:25,579 --> 00:08:26,673
Mother.

157
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,813
She's not wrong.

158
00:08:28,813 --> 00:08:31,678
Your career there was impressive.

159
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:33,079
Exactly.

160
00:08:34,053 --> 00:08:35,281
Gyeol, listen.

161
00:08:35,281 --> 00:08:38,080
I'm saying this not just as your father,

162
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,300
but as the CEO of Kangsu Construction.

163
00:08:41,079 --> 00:08:44,234
This competition between the two teams
isn't something...

164
00:08:44,234 --> 00:08:46,459
you can take on based solely
on filial duty to your grandfather.

165
00:08:46,952 --> 00:08:49,252
It requires a considerable amount
of company funds...

166
00:08:49,252 --> 00:08:51,934
and manpower, and on top of that...

167
00:08:51,934 --> 00:08:55,467
Are you asking me to drop out?

168
00:08:56,139 --> 00:08:58,934
Well, if participation is the goal,

169
00:08:58,934 --> 00:09:02,142
stepping back could be an option.

170
00:09:02,142 --> 00:09:05,311
Father, he's already in it.

171
00:09:06,220 --> 00:09:07,311
I'll think about it.

172
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:10,038
I'll excuse myself. Enjoy your meal.

173
00:09:17,814 --> 00:09:19,247
What's wrong with both of you?

174
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:20,827
What did we do?

175
00:09:21,673 --> 00:09:24,327
Are you doing this
because you think I'll lose to him?

176
00:09:24,953 --> 00:09:27,867
Are you trying to make him quit...

177
00:09:28,258 --> 00:09:30,136
and send him back to the U.S.?

178
00:09:30,313 --> 00:09:31,638
Watch your words.

179
00:09:31,638 --> 00:09:34,500
The more you act like this,
the more pathetic I feel.

180
00:09:35,239 --> 00:09:36,567
Why do you think
I can't compete with him...

181
00:09:36,567 --> 00:09:38,634
before we've even started?

182
00:09:40,359 --> 00:09:42,517
Hey, you! Ko Min Ho!

183
00:09:43,634 --> 00:09:44,718
That brat...

184
00:09:44,847 --> 00:09:47,534
What a day.

185
00:09:47,534 --> 00:09:48,834
So annoying.

186
00:09:50,747 --> 00:09:54,368
What? She said she's starting in 2030?
Really?

187
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,664
Total girl crush.

188
00:09:58,087 --> 00:09:59,966
No, more like "lady crush."

189
00:09:59,966 --> 00:10:02,867
I've never seen anyone
shut Min Ho's mom down like that.

190
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,368
It was so satisfying.

191
00:10:07,620 --> 00:10:08,753
You're so silly.

192
00:10:09,046 --> 00:10:11,578
You should've seen it.

193
00:10:11,813 --> 00:10:14,367
She kept pushing,
saying the center was her spot,

194
00:10:14,367 --> 00:10:16,034
and the look on her face...

195
00:10:21,354 --> 00:10:24,657
Is that developer adjusting well?

196
00:10:25,093 --> 00:10:26,759
The chairman is concerned.

197
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:29,896
Yes, she seems very adaptable.

198
00:10:30,253 --> 00:10:31,864
Like mother, like daughter.

199
00:10:32,886 --> 00:10:35,619
By the way,
why are you home so early today?

200
00:10:36,180 --> 00:10:37,971
The chairman had an evening engagement,

201
00:10:38,266 --> 00:10:39,539
so I drove him and came back.

202
00:10:40,133 --> 00:10:41,374
An evening engagement?

203
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:43,577
This is your wish?

204
00:10:44,806 --> 00:10:47,247
Dinner at a nice restaurant?

205
00:10:47,247 --> 00:10:49,349
Why? Don't you like it?

206
00:10:49,349 --> 00:10:51,251
Of course I do.

207
00:10:51,993 --> 00:10:53,847
I didn't want to seem foolish at my age,

208
00:10:54,519 --> 00:10:57,223
so I worked up a sweat
trying to hide the white outfit.

209
00:10:57,926 --> 00:10:59,392
Why hide it?

210
00:11:00,519 --> 00:11:01,932
You look beautiful.

211
00:11:04,813 --> 00:11:06,866
How do I look?

212
00:11:07,353 --> 00:11:08,643
Very handsome.

213
00:11:09,487 --> 00:11:11,520
More than Robert Redford.

214
00:11:12,220 --> 00:11:14,820
And you look like Audrey Hepburn.

215
00:11:15,846 --> 00:11:16,846
No,

216
00:11:17,334 --> 00:11:21,067
even more elegant and beautiful.

217
00:11:21,592 --> 00:11:22,926
Enough of that. Go ahead and eat.

218
00:11:30,799 --> 00:11:32,073
It's delicious.

219
00:11:42,033 --> 00:11:43,866
Let's just eat this and go home.

220
00:11:44,246 --> 00:11:46,546
Home is the most comfortable place.

221
00:11:46,547 --> 00:11:47,674
What are you talking about?

222
00:11:48,367 --> 00:11:51,167
We've barely started.

223
00:11:53,193 --> 00:11:54,647
Let me do it.

224
00:12:03,313 --> 00:12:04,780
Eat slowly,

225
00:12:05,886 --> 00:12:10,007
we have another place to go.
Just so you know.

226
00:12:10,631 --> 00:12:11,698
Where?

227
00:12:15,133 --> 00:12:18,067
Just eat.

228
00:12:19,119 --> 00:12:22,942
What? Dance classes
at the Kangsu Cultural Center?

229
00:12:22,942 --> 00:12:24,034
What should we do?

230
00:12:24,034 --> 00:12:26,716
What if something like today
happens again?

231
00:12:27,252 --> 00:12:29,667
Why is she doing something so unusual?

232
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:31,567
She took a survey at Kangsu Construction,

233
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:33,867
and they sent a class voucher as a gift.

234
00:12:34,892 --> 00:12:36,011
This is a problem.

235
00:12:36,526 --> 00:12:39,259
Find out her dance class schedule for me.

236
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:41,833
Okay. How was it today?

237
00:12:42,073 --> 00:12:43,339
How was the interview?

238
00:12:45,159 --> 00:12:46,366
It didn't go well.

239
00:12:48,459 --> 00:12:51,426
How about we just tell Mom everything now?

240
00:12:51,907 --> 00:12:54,813
I hate seeing you struggle like this.

241
00:12:56,293 --> 00:12:58,426
Let's wait for Eun Hyeong's results first.

242
00:13:09,289 --> 00:13:11,791
(Deposited to Cho Eun Ae, 250,000 dollars)

243
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:16,120
Eun Ae,

244
00:13:16,339 --> 00:13:18,839
what is this money? 250,000 dollars?

245
00:13:19,232 --> 00:13:21,666
It's from selling Lucky Joy Tech.

246
00:13:22,204 --> 00:13:25,071
You said you were scammed.
How did you get it back?

247
00:13:25,553 --> 00:13:27,953
I refused it before
to get the company back,

248
00:13:28,401 --> 00:13:30,143
but I just accepted it.
It's fair compensation.

249
00:13:30,813 --> 00:13:33,213
Good, very good.

250
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:35,579
At least it wasn't all for nothing.

251
00:13:37,459 --> 00:13:40,367
Think of it as five years of saved salary.

252
00:13:40,367 --> 00:13:42,000
Don't touch that money.

253
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:44,185
It'll be for your marriage.

254
00:13:44,185 --> 00:13:46,059
This isn't for marriage, Mom.

255
00:13:46,306 --> 00:13:48,427
You're not planning to spend it, are you?

256
00:13:48,933 --> 00:13:51,800
Absolutely not. Once you start using it,

257
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:53,480
it disappears fast.

258
00:13:54,203 --> 00:13:56,336
Okay, I'll handle it.

259
00:13:56,639 --> 00:14:00,306
If you live long enough,
you get to see days like this.

260
00:14:01,446 --> 00:14:02,479
Get some rest.

261
00:14:02,812 --> 00:14:05,211
Unbelievable girl.

262
00:14:09,626 --> 00:14:11,751
Now that I've secured the investment...

263
00:14:13,914 --> 00:14:16,080
I need to get access to the server
as soon as possible.

264
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,367
What is that team manager even doing?

265
00:14:18,367 --> 00:14:20,634
He needs to start something
for me to even try.

266
00:14:22,266 --> 00:14:23,657
His number should be in here somewhere.

267
00:14:43,649 --> 00:14:46,285
(Childish Bunny)

268
00:14:53,027 --> 00:14:55,461
What are you calling me at this hour,
Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

269
00:14:55,988 --> 00:14:57,062
Well...

270
00:14:58,299 --> 00:15:00,299
How did you recognize my number
right away?

271
00:15:00,803 --> 00:15:03,503
I told you before.
I got it through your father.

272
00:15:04,432 --> 00:15:06,147
So you saved it?

273
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,374
What do you need?

274
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:12,267
I just don't understand.

275
00:15:12,580 --> 00:15:15,355
This project is a competition
between Team One and Team Two, right?

276
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:16,600
So?

277
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:19,300
Team One is running around nonstop
with meetings,

278
00:15:19,634 --> 00:15:22,220
and I just can't understand
what our team is doing.

279
00:15:22,691 --> 00:15:24,891
Are we doing it or not?

280
00:15:24,891 --> 00:15:28,067
So, have you finished reviewing
the orientation materials?

281
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:30,263
What year was Kangsu Construction founded?

282
00:15:30,793 --> 00:15:31,900
What? Out of nowhere?

283
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:33,800
What was the name
of the first apartment they completed?

284
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:34,834
How many employees are there?

285
00:15:35,186 --> 00:15:37,867
Wait, is this some kind of memory test?

286
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:40,140
I already know your memory isn't great,

287
00:15:40,140 --> 00:15:42,460
and I don't understand why an intern...

288
00:15:42,460 --> 00:15:44,334
who hasn't even learned the basics yet...

289
00:15:44,334 --> 00:15:45,812
is so obsessed with the competition.

290
00:15:45,812 --> 00:15:47,046
Forget it.

291
00:15:47,916 --> 00:15:50,120
What exactly do you do during the day?

292
00:15:50,219 --> 00:15:53,119
You'll find out when the time comes.
If that's all, I'm hanging up.

293
00:15:54,166 --> 00:15:55,254
Wait...

294
00:15:56,199 --> 00:15:58,791
He's a classic T type.

295
00:15:59,326 --> 00:16:01,124
How can someone have no emotions?

296
00:16:06,294 --> 00:16:08,668
What's with the photo all of a sudden?

297
00:16:09,226 --> 00:16:11,137
I don't know what I was so busy with...

298
00:16:11,413 --> 00:16:14,307
that I couldn't even get you
into a wedding dress back then.

299
00:16:17,053 --> 00:16:20,646
Think of this as a vow renewal.

300
00:16:24,013 --> 00:16:25,113
I'm late, Chairman.

301
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:27,887
I couldn't find
the wild roses you requested,

302
00:16:28,593 --> 00:16:30,193
so I prepared chrysanthemums instead.

303
00:16:30,446 --> 00:16:31,446
Thank you.

304
00:16:32,586 --> 00:16:34,453
We can't skip the bouquet.

305
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:39,932
Honey.

306
00:16:47,241 --> 00:16:48,474
Are you ready?

307
00:16:49,386 --> 00:16:51,811
Relax and smile.

308
00:16:52,233 --> 00:16:53,880
Here we go.

309
00:16:55,599 --> 00:16:56,982
That's good.

310
00:17:00,365 --> 00:17:01,765
One more time.

311
00:17:02,726 --> 00:17:03,893
Two, three.

312
00:17:05,191 --> 00:17:06,660
That's it, well done.

313
00:17:08,994 --> 00:17:10,160
Thank you.

314
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:11,167
Not at all.

315
00:17:12,194 --> 00:17:13,566
Get up now.

316
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,902
Sir,

317
00:17:16,214 --> 00:17:19,305
while I'm still sitting,
please take a solo shot of me too.

318
00:17:19,772 --> 00:17:22,041
A solo shot? Sure.

319
00:17:22,366 --> 00:17:23,399
What will you use it for?

320
00:17:24,545 --> 00:17:25,612
My funeral portrait.

321
00:17:26,973 --> 00:17:30,483
- Sorry?
- I hate stiff, serious photos,

322
00:17:30,483 --> 00:17:33,419
so take one where I'm smiling brightly.

323
00:17:34,186 --> 00:17:36,753
Yes, of course. One moment.

324
00:17:41,173 --> 00:17:42,973
All right, here we go.

325
00:17:46,260 --> 00:17:47,433
Two, three.

326
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:55,007
Smile bigger.

327
00:17:57,376 --> 00:18:00,980
One last big, bright laugh...

328
00:18:12,527 --> 00:18:13,527
Next.

329
00:18:14,959 --> 00:18:15,959
Next.

330
00:18:17,059 --> 00:18:20,093
This one's my favorite.

331
00:18:20,980 --> 00:18:21,980
Very nice.

332
00:18:23,860 --> 00:18:25,460
What do you think, Yeong Hwa?

333
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:28,426
Yes, it turned out well.

334
00:18:39,085 --> 00:18:41,354
(Kangsu Construction)

335
00:18:44,860 --> 00:18:47,453
Team Manager, why are you here so early?

336
00:18:47,453 --> 00:18:48,961
What about you?

337
00:18:49,506 --> 00:18:52,406
I commute early...

338
00:18:52,406 --> 00:18:54,700
to avoid wasting time on the road.

339
00:18:55,673 --> 00:18:58,744
What's going on?
Is he finally going to work?

340
00:19:27,738 --> 00:19:29,339
Do you have something to say?

341
00:19:30,303 --> 00:19:31,370
Here.

342
00:19:34,419 --> 00:19:35,819
What is it?

343
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:40,980
You said to wear slippers comfortably
in the office.

344
00:19:41,552 --> 00:19:44,134
It looked like you didn't have any,

345
00:19:44,134 --> 00:19:45,918
so I bought an extra pair.

346
00:19:46,187 --> 00:19:48,154
They're really soft and comfy.

347
00:19:49,525 --> 00:19:51,791
You expect me to wear these in the office?

348
00:19:51,946 --> 00:19:52,946
Why not?

349
00:19:54,393 --> 00:19:56,559
You were born into money, weren't you?

350
00:19:56,906 --> 00:19:59,265
I guess you don't wear cheap slippers
like these.

351
00:19:59,959 --> 00:20:01,067
Then give them back.

352
00:20:01,535 --> 00:20:03,335
You can't take back what you gave.

353
00:20:06,172 --> 00:20:09,900
These days,
I really find myself agreeing...

354
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:12,960
with old sayings. Do you know which one?

355
00:20:14,047 --> 00:20:15,513
What are you going to say now?

356
00:20:15,513 --> 00:20:16,782
"The elder is never outdone
by the younger."

357
00:20:17,266 --> 00:20:19,868
The CPO is working day and night,

358
00:20:19,868 --> 00:20:22,121
pushing his team forward for the project.

359
00:20:22,121 --> 00:20:23,289
But you...

360
00:20:23,289 --> 00:20:24,734
Ms. Cho Eun Ae,

361
00:20:25,073 --> 00:20:27,963
there's something
I've been wanting to tell you.

362
00:20:28,529 --> 00:20:31,516
Being nosy can be a disease.

363
00:20:34,226 --> 00:20:35,463
Don't tell me you're heading out again.

364
00:20:35,767 --> 00:20:37,240
No, you can't go today.

365
00:20:37,413 --> 00:20:38,860
What are you doing? Move.

366
00:20:39,127 --> 00:20:40,234
If you're leaving,

367
00:20:40,234 --> 00:20:42,800
at least give me access
to Joy's server first.

368
00:20:43,113 --> 00:20:45,134
Do you think I joined...

369
00:20:45,134 --> 00:20:46,446
just to envy other teams' meetings?

370
00:20:46,580 --> 00:20:49,115
Did you accept the intern offer...

371
00:20:50,751 --> 00:20:52,351
because you have an ulterior motive?

372
00:20:52,592 --> 00:20:54,226
An ulterior motive?

373
00:20:54,646 --> 00:20:56,910
Do you not know what a developer does?

374
00:20:57,157 --> 00:20:58,634
I need access to the server...

375
00:20:58,634 --> 00:21:00,318
to do anything.

376
00:21:00,318 --> 00:21:02,334
I clearly said
this is the orientation period.

377
00:21:02,334 --> 00:21:04,285
This kind of obsession with the server...

378
00:21:04,472 --> 00:21:06,465
Obsession? What do you mean?

379
00:21:06,739 --> 00:21:07,931
Move.

380
00:21:08,266 --> 00:21:11,020
No, we need to work too.

381
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:13,239
- Seriously.
- Team Manager.

382
00:21:13,239 --> 00:21:14,940
- Move.
- No.

383
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,200
Team Manager!

384
00:21:23,150 --> 00:21:24,517
Good morning, Manager Seo.

385
00:21:24,517 --> 00:21:26,085
Good morning.

386
00:21:26,872 --> 00:21:28,070
What's going on?

387
00:21:28,726 --> 00:21:31,126
Why is our team manager like that?

388
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:33,888
Does he want to work or not?

389
00:21:34,527 --> 00:21:37,997
Try searching
"Young Architect of the Year."

390
00:21:38,367 --> 00:21:40,467
- Sorry?
- I'm saying he's not acting like that...

391
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:42,067
for no reason.

392
00:21:45,871 --> 00:21:48,174
(Young Architect of the Year)

393
00:21:48,174 --> 00:21:50,676
(Korean architect Ko Gyeol
wins U.S. Young Architect of the Year.)

394
00:21:54,914 --> 00:21:56,816
(Designing the world
with the aesthetics of silence...)

395
00:21:57,479 --> 00:22:00,479
"He was selected as this year's winner.

396
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:04,034
An exceptional achievement
for a Korean architect"...

397
00:22:08,333 --> 00:22:10,963
What? Not even a lecturer...

398
00:22:11,213 --> 00:22:13,487
Straight to a professorship interview?

399
00:22:13,487 --> 00:22:14,834
Yes, Mother.

400
00:22:14,834 --> 00:22:17,670
He passed the document screening
and has the final interview today.

401
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:20,300
He wanted to tell you
after everything was done,

402
00:22:20,766 --> 00:22:23,366
but you seemed so upset that day,
so I called.

403
00:22:23,366 --> 00:22:25,311
That's wonderful.

404
00:22:26,073 --> 00:22:27,673
I knew it.

405
00:22:28,099 --> 00:22:29,415
Thank you for calling.

406
00:22:31,193 --> 00:22:33,000
What should I do?

407
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,260
My goodness.

408
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:41,337
- You want me to wear this?
- Yes.

409
00:22:41,819 --> 00:22:43,834
I bought it for a junior's wedding,

410
00:22:43,834 --> 00:22:45,031
but you never wore it.

411
00:22:45,031 --> 00:22:46,811
It's a bit uncomfortable.

412
00:22:47,706 --> 00:22:49,473
Your taste is always great,

413
00:22:50,213 --> 00:22:52,779
but the shirt feels like
it's introducing itself.

414
00:22:53,586 --> 00:22:56,719
Does the shirt say, "Hello, I'm luxury?"

415
00:22:57,219 --> 00:22:58,600
Just wear it.

416
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:01,249
It feels like...

417
00:23:01,249 --> 00:23:03,829
my identity is being overtaken
by the brand.

418
00:23:03,966 --> 00:23:07,703
No one cares about your shirt's logo.

419
00:23:12,733 --> 00:23:14,067
That felt good.

420
00:23:14,067 --> 00:23:17,434
After a scrub, I feel refreshed.

421
00:23:18,287 --> 00:23:19,820
My shoulders feel better too.

422
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:23,602
If your shoulders hurt,
you should see a doctor.

423
00:23:23,602 --> 00:23:26,367
Even machines break down over time.

424
00:23:26,367 --> 00:23:29,727
It's natural for worn-out shoulders
to ache.

425
00:23:29,727 --> 00:23:31,677
I just need to take care of them gently.

426
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:33,112
What if it gets worse?

427
00:23:34,586 --> 00:23:35,586
Good grief.

428
00:23:36,506 --> 00:23:39,351
You should think about dating.

429
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:42,522
At your young age,

430
00:23:42,624 --> 00:23:45,691
are you going to keep hanging out here
forever?

431
00:23:46,353 --> 00:23:47,767
You and your nagging.

432
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:50,296
I'll handle my own love life.

433
00:23:50,296 --> 00:23:51,597
You brat.

434
00:23:54,593 --> 00:23:55,693
Back from the bathhouse?

435
00:23:56,287 --> 00:23:58,504
I wanted to go with you,

436
00:23:59,126 --> 00:24:01,126
but you seem busy these days.

437
00:24:01,126 --> 00:24:04,367
Right, with line dancing and all.

438
00:24:05,539 --> 00:24:07,212
Did something good happen?

439
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:10,093
Yes, but I won't tell you.

440
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:12,288
I might jinx it.

441
00:24:13,215 --> 00:24:16,067
Then don't show it.

442
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:17,840
Come over for lunch.

443
00:24:18,452 --> 00:24:21,560
I marinated a lot of meat the other day.

444
00:24:21,954 --> 00:24:22,973
I'll make bulgogi.

445
00:24:22,973 --> 00:24:25,164
Sounds good.

446
00:24:26,946 --> 00:24:29,449
So what happened that day?

447
00:24:29,870 --> 00:24:31,603
Did something happen?

448
00:24:31,603 --> 00:24:32,667
Yes.

449
00:24:32,873 --> 00:24:35,540
But today, it all worked out.

450
00:24:35,940 --> 00:24:38,506
Come over, I'll have food ready soon.

451
00:24:39,492 --> 00:24:43,682
She's hot one minute, cold the next.

452
00:25:00,639 --> 00:25:02,734
You checked if you got the money, right?

453
00:25:03,492 --> 00:25:04,492
Yes.

454
00:25:05,066 --> 00:25:07,573
Eun Ae. No, Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

455
00:25:08,979 --> 00:25:11,143
Can we be more comfortable as colleagues?

456
00:25:11,580 --> 00:25:14,413
I feel really awkward.

457
00:25:14,647 --> 00:25:17,313
You feel awkward with me?
I don't at all.

458
00:25:17,827 --> 00:25:20,088
And why do we need to be comfortable...

459
00:25:20,088 --> 00:25:22,015
when we're competing teams?

460
00:25:22,015 --> 00:25:23,701
Even if we're competing,

461
00:25:24,366 --> 00:25:26,124
we're still colleagues.

462
00:25:26,846 --> 00:25:28,368
Come on, we should...

463
00:25:28,368 --> 00:25:30,500
You keep saying "we."

464
00:25:30,906 --> 00:25:34,033
Don't use that word so casually.

465
00:25:34,147 --> 00:25:36,013
It's unpleasant to hear.

466
00:25:36,013 --> 00:25:39,434
Hey,
how long are you going to act like this?

467
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:44,643
Mr. Han Ji Hun,

468
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:47,277
do you share server access too?

469
00:25:47,277 --> 00:25:48,547
What?

470
00:25:48,547 --> 00:25:51,216
How is a developer supposed to work
without server access?

471
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:54,200
What's going on here?

472
00:25:54,906 --> 00:25:57,523
I didn't call you,
yet you came to my office.

473
00:25:58,646 --> 00:26:01,626
I think I made a mistake
with the team setup request last time.

474
00:26:02,095 --> 00:26:03,128
I apologize.

475
00:26:03,599 --> 00:26:05,600
So should I take that...

476
00:26:05,600 --> 00:26:08,100
as you having no complaints
about the team now?

477
00:26:09,053 --> 00:26:12,471
It's my policy
not to bring personal feelings into work.

478
00:26:13,793 --> 00:26:16,159
I'll take it you've accepted my apology.

479
00:26:17,319 --> 00:26:18,319
Thank you, Seung Ri.

480
00:26:19,380 --> 00:26:22,681
Whether you have complaints or not,
thank you for staying with us.

481
00:26:24,626 --> 00:26:25,918
Come on, work with me here.

482
00:26:26,606 --> 00:26:28,672
I really want to do well in this race.

483
00:26:30,453 --> 00:26:32,191
See you in the meeting room
in ten minutes.

484
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:54,146
What are you working on so hard?

485
00:26:55,250 --> 00:26:57,850
I'm compiling data
on retirement communities worldwide.

486
00:26:58,886 --> 00:27:01,386
You were doing something really important.

487
00:27:03,220 --> 00:27:04,753
I need to go to the archives.

488
00:27:04,753 --> 00:27:05,754
Okay.

489
00:27:10,607 --> 00:27:13,490
It looked like he was preparing something.

490
00:27:19,672 --> 00:27:20,906
Did he leave it on?

491
00:27:22,220 --> 00:27:23,953
What is he working on?

492
00:27:29,346 --> 00:27:32,455
So he's been going around taking photos?

493
00:27:35,540 --> 00:27:36,589
Not bad.

494
00:27:44,079 --> 00:27:45,079
What is this?

495
00:27:45,353 --> 00:27:47,132
What are you doing?

496
00:28:04,416 --> 00:28:07,386
(Our Happy Days)

497
00:28:07,386 --> 00:28:10,289
Do you think this is your playground
where you can run wild as you please?

498
00:28:10,439 --> 00:28:11,523
I'm sorry.

499
00:28:11,753 --> 00:28:14,553
I've still got a long way to go, Dad.

500
00:28:15,020 --> 00:28:16,472
A real estate lady?

501
00:28:16,472 --> 00:28:19,064
It's called a licensed realtor.

502
00:28:19,064 --> 00:28:21,300
What? Do you know who I am?

503
00:28:21,300 --> 00:28:22,935
We have a team dinner tonight.

504
00:28:22,935 --> 00:28:25,003
Is that something I have to attend?

505
00:28:25,326 --> 00:28:26,500
Hang in there.

506
00:28:26,500 --> 00:28:28,907
Just until I pull my baby out of this.

507
00:28:28,908 --> 00:28:30,576
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
